This is Uranium-235, the rock star of radioactive elements. It’s unstable, cranky, and dangerous—basically my spirit animal. 
Let's hit it with a neutron, and it  will split into smaller nuclei, releasing energy and more neutrons. That’s fission, the phenomenon that powers everything from reactors to regrettable explosions.
